test_nbody.cpp tests the NBODY algorithm of NVIDIA SDK

It is highly recommanded to use it before using Simbuca V3.0 with NBODY algorithm.

How to use it:
- in Makefile, set the good PATH of CUDA include. (by default /usr/local/cuda/include)
- compilation with make

then launch 
./test_nbody Npart Niteration options 
Npart is the number of particles (2^n)
Niteration is the number of calculation 

options: 
benchmark : returns the performance of the NBODY algorithm
cpu : compares the results with the CPU calculation
sync : use synchronised mode of the NBODY algorithm (it's slower), asynchronised mode is by default)

examples
./test_nbody 1024 100 benchmark cpu 

        NBODY test for SIMBUCA V3.0
        Number of particles : 1024
        Number of iteration : 100
        Asynchro mode enable
        Benchmark mode enable
        Comparison with CPU calculation

